Poetry - Building & Publishing

Manage dependencies in your Python project with [prgm]poetry[/prgm]. Use the [prgm]build[/prgm] subcommand to build the package, and the [prgm]publish[/prgm] subcommand to publish it to the package registry.

Building & Publishing a Package

$ [prgm]poetry build[/prgm]                       # Build source and wheel distributions
$ [prgm]poetry publish[/prgm]

Adding a new Publishable Package Registry

$ [prgm]poetry config[/prgm] [arg-value]repositories.testpypi[/arg-value] [arg-value]https://test.pypi.org/legacy/[/arg-value]
$ [prgm]poetry config[/prgm] [arg-value]http-basic.foo[/arg-value] [arg-value]<username>[/arg-value] [arg-value]<password>[/arg-value]  # Credentials stored in system keychain
